<HEADLINE>
<P>
PETE SCHABARUM ON TERM LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Willie Brown's threat to punish the handful of Assembly members who supported 
Prop. 140 by making the first cuts in these legislators' staffs aptly 
demonstrates the vindictive and business-as-usual approach to government which 
has Californians so fed up with Sacramento. Term limits may not be the panacea 
for California's legislative ills, but it might do us all some good to 
ultimately be rid of Brown. 
</P>
<P>
MARK E. "EAGAN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
