<HEADLINE>
<P>
PETE SCHABARUM ON TERM LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I read with a good deal of amusement Pete Schabarum's defense of Prop. 140 ("A 
Change That Opens State's Political Doors," Commentary, Nov. 13). No doubt 
Schabarum is well-qualified to describe the perils arising from the seniority 
of elected officeholders -- here's someone whose snout and hoofs have been in 
the public trough for several decades. 
</P>
<P>
Now, in an ironic twist, Schabarum has anointed himself as the keeper of the 
public conscience, purse and morality -- with a good deal less justification 
than those in Sacramento he has chosen to attack. Schabarum has now served five 
terms as a member of the Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors. I would like 
to know why Schabarum was an active participant in promoting the same type of 
empire-building, self-perpetuation and irresponsibility in the county that he 
decries in the Legislature. 
</P>
<P>
LEON COOPER 
</P>
<P>
Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
