<HEADLINE>
<P>
'TEACHING AMERICA' LESSONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Teach for America is a valuable program that should be pursued. 
</P>
<P>
Despite the many arguments against the program, the advantages outweigh the 
defaults. 
</P>
<P>
Some critics argue that the cost is too much. Like any business, one must 
invest in order to succeed. Others have disapproved because of the inexperience 
of the teachers. This may be true, but a with all new teachers, time will ease 
the tensions and facilitate the teaching process. 
</P>
<P>
As a student, I believe that the earlier people finish their educations and 
enter the professional fields, the more zeal and love they (will) have for 
their jobs. 
</P>
<P>
KATHIE H. KIM 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
