<HEADLINE>
<P>
BLACK COLLEGE BONANZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your decision to run the article "Black Colleges Enjoy Renaissance" was greatly 
appreciated by us. The article meant so much to the continuance and growth of 
our program, the purpose of which is to expose Black youth to a very positive 
and motivational experience. 
</P>
<P>
As a result of the article in The Times, new doors have opened to us, doors we 
didn't even know existed. 
</P>
<P>
We received a call from Mr. Randy St. Martin of the L.A. Theatre Center, who 
would like to perform his one-man show "Color Me Black" at the Theatre Center 
during Black History Month and donate the proceeds to the Black College Tours. 
With the money raised, we intend to offer scholarships at high schools 
throughout the Los Angeles and Compton unified school districts. 
</P>
<P>
The United Negro College Fund called to say that any individual or corporation 
wishing to make a donation to help sponsor a student's tour could do so. Thus, 
they are setting up a restricted fund with all monies collected to be earmarked 
for Black College Tours. 
</P>
<P>
We would like to thank Ms. Jocelyn Stewart for the outstanding job that she did 
on the article. With this type of help, we are certain that we will be able to 
continue to have a positive impact on the lives of the youth of our community. 
</P>
<P>
GREGORY and YASMIN DELAHOUSSAYE 
</P>
<P>
Sepulveda 
</P>
</TEXT>
