<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oh Say Can You See: President Bush told American troops in the Persian Gulf 
Thursday that he has a secret weapon -- Roseanne Barr. 
</P>
<P>
Standing before the camouflage-clad troops with his wife, Barbara, Bush said, 
"You'll be glad to know that if it goes on too long, we have a secret weapon in 
reserve. If push comes to shove, we're going to get Roseanne Barr to go to Iraq 
and sing the national anthem. Baghdad Betty, eat your heart out." Television 
personality Barr received much bad press for an off-putting rendition of the 
national anthem before a major-league baseball game in San Diego last summer. 
BETH KLEID 
</P>
