<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Disney Deal: The creators of ABC's "The Wonder Years," husband-and-wife team 
Neal Marlens and Carol Black, signed an exclusive deal to create movies and 
television shows for Walt Disney Studios. The agreement, rumored earlier this 
fall but officially announced this week by Disney, calls for the couple to be 
involved in projects for four years. The financial terms of the deal weren't 
released, but early reports estimate the couple will be paid at least $15 
million. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
