<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Safe Sex Pitch: A public-service announcement urging couples to use condoms for 
safer sex and AIDS prevention, which was refused by several television 
networks, will be tagged onto the beginning of at least one film in the video 
market. The spot will appear at the start of the tape of "Longtime Companion," 
a film that chronicled the emergence of AIDS during the '80s among a group of 
New Yorkers. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
