</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mobil Loses Wrongful-Dismissal Case: Mobil Corp. said it will appeal a decision 
by a federal court that found a subsidiary had wrongfully dismissed 
environmental officer Valcar Bowman Jr. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. District Court in Newark, N.J., had ordered Mobil Chemical Co. to pay 
Bowman $375,000 in compensatory damages and $1 million in punitive damages. 
Bowman charged that Mobil dismissed him because he would not whitewash reports 
documenting Mobil's environmental problems, an act that would have violated 
federal and state environmental laws. Mobil said Bowman's 1986 dismissal was 
part of a cost cutting program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
