<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MYSTERIES R US: Doug Stumpf, senior editor at William Morrow &amp; Co. in New 
York, says the county is the setting for so many mysteries because it's 
"perfect" -- suburban, but with "the crime and sophistication of an urban 
center." Besides, "there's something about a hotter climate and the beach and 
palm trees that gives it a really sexy element you don't get if your feet are 
in the snow." . . . And judging from the manuscripts Stumpf sees, "there's a 
lot of talent coming out of Orange County these days." 
</P>
</TEXT>
