CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
THERMAL; 
</P>
<P>
VOLUNTEERS SEARCH FOR MISSING PLANE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forty volunteers in 22 airplanes searched in vain Thursday over the California 
and Arizona desert for a small plane carrying a 57-year-old Thousand Oaks pilot 
and his passenger. The search for William Crimmins and Lavonne DeSchpper, last 
seen Monday evening when they left an airport at Grand Junction, Colo., will 
continue today, according to Civic Air Patrol spokesman Ed Crankshaw. 
</P>
