<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
SCAVENGING BANNED AT RECYCLING BINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has approved an ordinance prohibiting scavenging from 
recycling bins that will be used for the city's curbside recycling program that 
begins next month. 
</P>
<P>
"We had to take the precaution," said Mayor Christian W. Keena. 
</P>
<P>
"We had some concerns about people going through the city in trucks and 
emptying the curbside bins." 
</P>
<P>
Those violating the ordinance would be guilty of a misdemeanor and subject to a 
fine and jail time, said Damian Hopp, assistant city manager. Other county 
cities, including Irvine, have adopted similar municipal laws. 
</P>
<P>
Income from sale of recycled materials will help pay for the program, which is 
scheduled to begin Dec. 17, said City Manager Fred Sorsabal. 
</P>
<P>
"With the scavenging ordinance we are establishing a means of dealing with a 
potential abuse of the recycling program if action becomes necessary," he 
said.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
