<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: WHITAKER RETAINS TITLE, BEATING MARQUEZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pernell Whitaker, of Norfolk, Va., retained his world lightweight title with a 
unanimous decision over Benji Marquez of Puerto Rico Thursday in a championship 
boxing doubleheader at Madrid. 
</P>
<P>
Whitaker, a left-hander, piled up an insurmountable lead in points with his 
stinging right jabs and bloodied Marquez's face with powerful left hooks to win 
for the 25th time in 26 pro fights. 
</P>
<P>
Also on the card, World Boxing Assn. cruiserweight champion Robert Daniels 
retained his crown by fighting to a draw with former champion Taoufik Belbouli. 
</P>
<P>
Belbouli, the French-Tunisian former champion, dominated the middle rounds of 
the 12-round fight, but Daniels rallied in the last two rounds to keep his 
title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
