<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAY WINS HIS 5,000TH IN CHURCHILL FEATURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOUISVILLE, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jockey Pat Day rode his 5,000th winner in a feature race at Churchill Downs 
Thursday, becoming the 12th jockey to reach the milestone. 
</P>
<P>
The victory came in the $100,000 Falls City Handicap, a 1 1/8-mile race for 
fillies and mares 3 years old and older. 
</P>
<P>
Day was aboard Screen Prospect, which paid $5.80, $3.80 and $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
"It was really special to win here. It would have been special anywhere, but to 
win it here at Churchill Downs -- we've had such a tremendous amount of success 
here and we've got such a large following as regards the fans," Day said. 
</P>
<P>
"The only thing, I guess, we haven't done here is win the Derby and we're 
looking forward to doing that in '91." 
</P>
<P>
Day is Churchill Downs' all-time leading rider. The track will donate a total 
of $5,000 to Sts. Mary and Elizabeth Hospital and to Kosair Children's 
Hospital, both in Louisville, in Day's name, according to a statement issued by 
the track. 
</P>
</TEXT>
