<P>
EX-COP SHOOTS ARMED INTRUDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A retired police officer shot and critically wounded three of four armed men 
last night after they burst into his home brandishing handguns at him, police 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Police identified the intruders as Phouxay Vanhnarath, 19, of Costa Mesa; 
Sayavong Nanthavongdouangsy, 18, of Anaheim, and two male juveniles -- one of 
Garden Grove and one of Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
The names of the juveniles were being withheld because of their age. 
</P>
<P>
Vanhnarath and the two juveniles, who were hit by shotgun fire, were in 
critical condition at UCI Medical Center in Orange, Anaheim Police Sgt. Chet 
Barry said. 
</P>
<P>
Nanthavongdouangsy was being held at the Anaheim Temporary Detention Facility 
on suspicion of attempted residential robbery, Barry said. 
</P>
<P>
Earl Swoap, 53, who retired from the Yakima, Wash., police force 13 years ago, 
told police he fired at the intruders after they broke into his North Hanover 
Street home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
