<P>
MAN FIRES 100 ROUNDS IN HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man armed with a shotgun and boxes of ammunition fired about 100 rounds 
through the walls of his Hollywood home this morning, terrifying neighbors and 
triggering a four-hour standoff, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Roy Koutsky, 25, surrendered to police about 5:30 a.m. as police warned him 
over a loudspeaker that a SWAT team was about to storm the bullet-riddled house 
in the 1300 block of N. Gordon Avenue, Sgt. Pat Findley said. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured by the shots fired and no other structures were hit, 
although many of the shots penetrated the walls of Koutsky's residence. 
</P>
<P>
A search of the house produced a 12-gauge shotgun, a replica of an Uzi rifle, a 
pair of handcuffs, a sword and boxes of ammunition, Findley said. 
</P>
