<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
U.S. POSTS $31.4-BILLION DEFICIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States posted a budget deficit of $31.46 billion in October in the 
opening month of fiscal 1991, the Treasury Department reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The shortfall follows a surplus of $20.84 billion in September and a deficit of 
$26.08 billion in October, 1989, according to the department's regular budget 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
Last month's outlays totaled $110.17 billion, while receipts totaled $78.71 
billion, the government said. 
</P>
<P>
Under the category "contribution to the defense cooperation account," the 
government received $1.62 billion in October, mainly for the Operation Desert 
Shield buildup in the Persian Gulf. Overall defense spending totaled $24.09 
billion for the month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
