P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
LLOYDS REVEALS CUTTING 2,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lloyds Bank PLC said today it has cut 2,000 staff this year as part of an 
ongoing review of its banking operations. 
</P>
<P>
The cuts came mostly through natural attrition and early retirement throughout 
the company, including head office staff, it said. 
</P>
<P>
Lloyds, one of Britain's largest commercial banks, currently employs 55,000. 
</P>
<P>
Further job cuts are expected in the future, but the exact numbers haven't been 
decided, said a spokesman, who was not identified in keeping with bank 
practice. 
</P>
<P>
Other British banks also have been trimming staff and consolidating branch 
networks in a bid to reduce operating costs and bolster profitability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
