SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
AIDS PATIENT DIES RUNNING RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An AIDS patient running in the Atlanta Half Marathon on Thursday died of heart 
failure near the end of the race. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Barden, 37, of Stone Mountain was running in the middle of the 
5,000-runner pack when he collapsed in the 11th mile of the 13.1-mile race. 
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Track Club spokeswoman Julia Emmons said efforts to revive Barden on 
the sidewalk failed. 
</P>
<P>
Barden was not a member of the club, which sponsors the annual Thanksgiving 
Atlanta Marathon, 26.2 miles, and the Half Marathon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
