<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIZ SMITH: BETWEEN WORKOUTS, TYSON LIKES TO PARTY LIKE A CHAMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LIZ SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MIKE TYSON is training at Atlantic City's Trump Plaza. The former heavyweight 
champ fights Alex Stewart on Dec. 9. Tyson, however, does believe that all work 
and no play makes Mike a dull boy. 
</P>
<P>
Tyson recently caught a performance by the O'Jays at Trop World. The group 
spotted the big guy in the audience and pulled him up onstage, introducing him 
as "the newest member of our group." The champ then joined them in a song. 
</P>
<P>
Before this, Tyson turned up at the Trump Plaza showcase for the former Miss 
America, Suzette Charles. Suzette, who has never wanted to reign alone like 
Garbo, told her audience that she and the former champ were "more than just 
good friends." That may indeed be true, but it wasn't Suzette who then 
accompanied Mike on an upscale boutique shopping spree on the Boardwalk wherein 
he spent $40,000 on clothes for himself and an unidentified lady friend. Tyson 
has also been seen cruising Atlantic City in his bright red Ferrari, a tall and 
gorgeous blond beside him. 
</P>
<P>
I love to see young people having a good time, don't you? 
</P>
<P>
LYRICIST FRED Ebb and composer John Kander ("Cabaret," "Chicago," "Flora the 
Red Menace") are rewriting their 1977 Broadway musical "The Act" for the 
talented Dorothy Loudon. Liza Minnelli originated the role of a famous singer 
making a Las Vegas comeback, involved with an older man. She won a Tony award 
for her tour de force performance. 
</P>
<P>
Among the revisions for the new star is a change to show an older woman's 
infatuation for a younger man. 
</P>
<P>
THE CARNEGIE DELI in Beverly Hills is booked solid for a private party to be 
held the night of Jan. 20, 1996. That's the day George Burns will turn 100. 
</P>
</TEXT>
